description:
&lt;p&gt;Derbyshire Healthcare NHS FT is looking to recruit an Admin Support Worker to join a new developing service within the north of Derbyshire.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post will be 37.5 hours per week, covering two areas.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;One area is the High Peak and Derbyshire Dales based at Newholme Hospital in Bakewell.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The other are will be covering Chesterfield, Bolsover and North East of the county, currently based at Walton Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A single post holder will need to divide their time; considering need and travel between the two bases.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We would consider a job share between part time candidates. Please state your preferred hours on the application.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post is for the older people&#39;s in-reach and home treatment team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The primary goal of the service is to support people within their own homes who are experiencing a breakdown of their mental health.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will effectively deliver a comprehensive, high quality administrative service and provide a professional first point of contact for people making contact with the service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience of administration support is essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Personal development will be supported and encouraged through IPR, regular supervision and access to training opportunities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Anna Bennett, Service Manager, High Peak and Dales, 01629 817895, anna.bennett4@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;or&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lynsey Cockerton, Interim Service Manager, Chesterfield and North East Derbyshire, 01246 515090 / 01629 817888, lynsey.cockerton@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
